#DEFAULT ARGUMENTS
#  We can provide a default value while creating a function.
#  This way the function assumes a default value even if a value is not provided
#  in the function call for that argument.

'''def average(a=5, b=5): 
 print("The average is", (a+b)/2)

#average(5) It will be the value of a
#for b it is average(b= "your value")
average(10,8)'''

